{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1391"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of knitted and crocheted fabrics"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1391"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :knitting/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :labor-standards :materials-traceability]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :knitting-mill-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "KnittingAdvisor ⊣ Knitting Mill Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for knitted/crocheted-fabric manufacturing (circular knitting,
 flat knitting, crocheting lines, yarn quality) -- not direct
 knitting/crocheting-line control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct knitting/
 crocheting-machine control), permanent direct-operate block,
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-volume recompute against
 the batch's own logged yardage, double-schedule guard, quality-grade
 validation, and defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern
 flagging (materials-safety / equipment-safety) ALWAYS escalates to a
 human mill supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op
 eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
